<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,446,1112]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authority=": Thompson &amp; Pont (1994: 74)" authorityName=": Thompson &amp; Pont" authorityPageNumber="74" authorityYear="1994" box="[151,651,998,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favillacea">
<emphasis box="[151,326,998,1021]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<collectingRegion box="[151,219,1000,1021]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Musca</collectingRegion>
favillacea
</emphasis>
: Thompson &amp; Pont (1994: 74)
</taxonomicName>
. These authors assigned the name as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[1188,1432,998,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ieiuna">
<emphasis box="[1188,1327,1000,1021]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<collectingRegion box="[1188,1256,1000,1021]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Musca</collectingRegion>
ieiuna
</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
, even though they referred to Townsend (1931b: 371), who misidentified the 
<typeStatus box="[999,1092,1029,1051]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Thompson &amp; Pont" authorityYear="1994" box="[1130,1306,1029,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favillacea">
<emphasis box="[1130,1306,1029,1051]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<collectingRegion box="[1130,1197,1030,1051]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Musca</collectingRegion>
favillacea
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Bengalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Bengalia lateralis</emphasis>
Macquart
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1819" box="[425,698,1060,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torosa">
<emphasis box="[425,564,1061,1082]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<collectingRegion box="[425,493,1061,1082]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Musca</collectingRegion>
torosa
</emphasis>
Wiedemann
</taxonomicName>
]. They cited the specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[999,1095,1061,1082]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">NHMUK</collectionCode>
as “HT 
<specimenCount box="[1182,1199,1060,1082]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
”, following Townsend (1931b).
</paragraph>
